{"title":"microSHIFT Launches Uber Affordable Sword Black Gravel Group","link":"https://bikerumor.com/microshift-sword-black-gravel-group/","date":1719388800000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-real-hero.jpeg\" width=\"1280\" height=\"1070\" alt=\"(Photos/microSHIFT)\" /></p>\n<p>Known for making “bike parts for reality”, microSHIFT just released a new, even more affordable version of their popular <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/microshift-sword-gravel-bike-drivetrains/\" target=\"_blank\">Sword Gravel Group</a>. Meet Sword Black. Even though slapping the “Black” moniker on a product usually means that it’s more pricy, that’s not the case here. The new Sword Black is meant to “fill out” microSHIFT’s product line, reaching more riders and offering an even more attainable price point.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group Hero2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-Hero2-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a><figcaption>(Photos/microSHIFT)</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Samsies as OG Sword</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group rear cassete\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-cassete-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group made for flared bars\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-made-for-flared-bars-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Sword Black offers a lot of the same features that the OG Sword has, including:</p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Lower gear ranges than comparable road groups (2×11-38t, 1×11-46t)</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Dialed ergonomics that feel good on flared bars </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Easy to work on yourself. (microSHIFT has a full suite of YouTube videos on the matter) </li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h2>Here’s Where Sword Black Differs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group rear der\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-rear-der-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"854\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group 2x crank on bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike-297x198.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike-120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike-768x512.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike-800x533.jpeg 800w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-crank-on-bike-720x480.jpeg 720w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>It runs 9 speeds instead of 10 speeds</li>\n\n\n\n<li>There is no clutch</li>\n\n\n\n<li>It uses a square taper crank</li>\n\n\n\n<li>The groupset is $126 cheaper at retail of $349 vs $474 (including crankset)</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-on-complete-bike-e1719336462411.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"595\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-on-complete-bike-e1719336462411.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group 2x on complete bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-on-complete-bike-e1719336462411.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-on-complete-bike-e1719336462411-297x138.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-on-complete-bike-e1719336462411-120x56.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x-on-complete-bike-e1719336462411-768x357.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<h2>Same Cable Pull</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-right-hand-shifter.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-right-hand-shifter.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group right hand shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-right-hand-shifter.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-right-hand-shifter-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-right-hand-shifter-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-right-hand-shifter-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-left-shifter.jpeg\"><img width=\"1280\" height=\"1280\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-left-shifter.jpeg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group left shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-left-shifter.jpeg 1280w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-left-shifter-297x297.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-left-shifter-120x120.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-left-shifter-768x768.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<p>Both Sword and Sword Black use the same cable pull ratio, making the rear derailleurs for each group cross-compatible… geez, what a novel idea. Imagine if you already have the Sword Black group and wanted to upgrade to the Sword rear derailleur, you could do so without changing anything else. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>1x &amp; 2x Sword Black Group Scecs</h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-1x-specs.jpg\"><img width=\"990\" height=\"465\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-1x-specs.jpg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group 1x9 specs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-1x-specs.jpg 990w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-1x-specs-297x140.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-1x-specs-120x56.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-1x-specs-768x361.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>1x specifications</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x9-specs.jpg\"><img width=\"1003\" height=\"500\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x9-specs.jpg\" alt=\"microSHIFT Sword Black Gravel Group 2x9 specs\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x9-specs.jpg 1003w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x9-specs-297x148.jpg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x9-specs-120x60.jpg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/06/microSHIFT-Sword-Black-Gravel-Group-2x9-specs-768x383.jpg 768w\" /></a><figcaption>2x specifications</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>microSHIFT calls both of the Sword Gravel groups “modern components with an analog soul”. I like it. <br /><br />Check out everything microSHIFT has to offer by hitting the link below. </p>\n\n\n\n<p><em><a href=\"https://www.microshift.com/us/\">microShift.com</a></em></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/microshift-sword-black-gravel-group/\">microSHIFT Launches Uber Affordable Sword Black Gravel Group</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Ron Frazelle","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"f859dfa2b1b13b75de2602e5f0b6bb77adf98dd38405117c5610c013f9926a48","category":"Cycling"}